      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is HiKOKI MultiVolt and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>MultiVolt</strong> is HiKOKI's innovative battery system. A single MultiVolt battery automatically delivers <strong>36V</strong> when used in MultiVolt tools and steps down to <strong>18V</strong> when used in standard 18V HiKOKI tools. No adaptors, no compromise — just slot in and the battery adjusts to the tool.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are old Hitachi batteries compatible with HiKOKI tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — HiKOKI 18V slide-type batteries are fully compatible with Hitachi 18V slide-type tools (and vice versa). The battery design is identical; only the brand name changed. <strong>MultiVolt batteries also work in older 18V Hitachi tools</strong>, making the transition seamless.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is HiKOKI the same as Hitachi?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes — HiKOKI <em>is</em> Hitachi Power Tools, rebranded in 2018 following a corporate restructure. The engineering team, factory locations and product quality are identical. The name is new, but the Japanese engineering excellence is the same as it has been since 1948.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do HiKOKI tools come with?",
            "answer": "<p>HiKOKI power tools come with a <strong>3-year warranty</strong> when purchased from an authorised dealer. MultiVolt batteries carry an extraordinary <strong>lifetime warranty</strong> when registered online. As an authorised HiKOKI dealer, Invicta Tools handles all warranty claims directly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does HiKOKI compare to Makita and DeWalt?",
            "answer": "<p>HiKOKI sits alongside Makita and DeWalt as a genuine professional-grade alternative. The key differentiators are the <strong>MultiVolt dual-voltage system</strong>, the <strong>lifetime battery warranty</strong> and the <strong>competitive pricing</strong>. Many tradespeople are switching to HiKOKI for the value proposition without sacrificing performance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you stock HiKOKI batteries and chargers?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We carry the full range of HiKOKI batteries including <strong>MultiVolt 36V/18V</strong> in 2.5Ah and 4.0Ah, plus <strong>standard 18V</strong> batteries and <strong>rapid chargers</strong>. All available with free next-day delivery on orders over £30.</p>"
